'''Blue Ridge''' is a [[hamlet (place)|hamlet]] in [[Alberta]], [[Canada]].

It is located on [[Alberta Highway 658|Highway 658]], which runs north from [[Alberta Highway 43|Highway 43]] at the Cottonwood Station. It is established close to the [[Athabasca River]], between the towns of [[Whitecourt, Alberta|Whitecourt]] and [[Mayerthorpe, Alberta|Mayerthorpe]], an hour and a half away from [[Edmonton]].

The hamlet is administered by [[Woodlands County, Alberta|Woodlands County]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.municipalaffairs.gov.ab.ca/cfml/profiles/data/0480_1.htm|author=Alberta Municipal Affairs|title=Woodlands County - County Profile|accessdate=2008-06-26}}</ref>

==Demographics==
The community had a total population of 230 living in 97 dwellings in 2001.<ref name=indcan>{{Cite web | url= http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/webarchives/2006/http://broadband.gc.ca/demographic_servlet/community_demographics/434 | title= Blue Ridge community profile|author=Industry Canada/Web Achieve| authorlink=Industry Canada | accessdate= 2008-06-26}}</ref> The community has a land area of {{km2 to mi2|2.99|abbr=yes|wiki=yes}} and a [[population density]] of {{Pop density km2 to mi2|77.0| spell=UK | abbr=yes}}.

